# Architecture

This repository is a PNPM workspace with two packages:

- app/ (dineros-app): Nuxt 4 application with frontend and Nitro server (H3)
- microservice/: companion service for specialized operations (encryption rotate/migrate, background helpers)

Both use Prisma against MySQL 8, with prisma-field-encryption for field-level encryption support.

## app/ structure (selected)

- app/app.vue, pages/*, components/*: Vue 3 UI
- app/composables/*: client composables (useAPI/useAppFetch, categories, snapshot state, etc.)
- app/lib/*: shared utilities (formatting, rounding, filters, errors), plus test coverage in app/lib/__tests__
- app/schema/*: zod schemas (schema/zod.ts) and schema/plaid.ts
- app/plugins/*: Nuxt plugins (API init, store init, snapshot menu, LastPass workaround)
- app/middleware/*: Nuxt route middleware (auth, admin)
- app/server/
  - api/*: H3 handlers (REST-like, method in filename suffix)
  - clients/*: prismaClient, redisClient, queuesClient, postmarkClient, natsClient, openaiClient
  - lib/*: request helpers, error handling, auth/session utilities, access control, pagination, rate limiting, Plaid helpers, RSA/JWT helpers, etc.
  - services/*: business logic modules
    - PlaidSyncService, TransactionMatchingService, PlaidReauth, PlaidSyncNotificationService
    - Forecast engine modules under services/forecast/* (see Forecast section)
    - Reports, reconciliation, notifications, workspace/account services
    - Crypto/asset valuation: AlchemyService, AssetValueEstimateService
  - queues/*: BullMQ queues (plaidSync, plaidSyncBalance, recalculate, backup)
  - cron/*: nuxt-cron job definitions (plaid, recalculate, balance sync, backups)
  - repositories/*: accountListsRepository (singleton + impl)
  - routes/*: health probes and _nuxt asset route, sitemap
  - middleware/*: server-side auth enforcement and sitemap redirect
  - env.ts, envSchema.ts: runtime env validation (Zod)
  - logger.ts: Winston logging setup, Google Cloud integration ready
- app/prisma/
  - schema.prisma: authoritative schema (rich finance domain + crypto + logs)
  - migrations/*: SQL migrations
  - prismaClient.ts: Prisma client wrapper
  - reencrypt/*: auto-generated encryption migrators
  - seed.ts: test/dev seed data
- app/tests & app/pages/__tests__ & app/server/**/__tests__: Vitest; app/tests/e2e: Playwright

## microservice/ structure (selected)

- server.ts: H3/Nitro server entry
- routes/*.ts: migrate.get/post.ts and test.get.ts endpoints (simple operational surface)
- clients/*: prismaClient.ts, redisClient.ts
- lib/bull.ts: BullMQ setup
- prisma/: separate schema with subset of main app entities; reencrypt/* generated migrators
- scripts/k8s-rotate-db-key.sh: in-cluster key rotation helper (Dockerfile target runner-keyrotate)

## Data and flows

- Frontend → API: UI calls app/server/api/* handlers via ofetch/nuxt fetch (see app/plugins/api.ts, app/composables/useAPI.ts/useAppFetch.ts)
- API → Services → DB/Queues: Handlers validate input (Zod), enforce auth (server/middleware/auth.ts, requireAdmin.ts), and call services. Services read/write via server/clients/prismaClient.ts, enqueue work in server/clients/queuesClient.ts (BullMQ), or call Plaid/OpenAI/Alchemy
- Background: queues/* process jobs; nuxt-cron schedules periodic tasks under server/cron/*
- Forecast engine: services/forecast/* orchestrates computation using cache (ModernCacheService) and typed modules; persisted via DataPersisterService
- Encryption: prisma-field-encryption handles model field encryption; reencrypt/* migrators support key rotations. JWT and RSA services back auth and key rotation utilities
- Crypto: AlchemyService syncs balances/prices for EVM chains (see EvmChain, CryptoRegisterChain, CryptoTokenBalance models and cron/crypto-balance.hourly.ts)

## Notable runtime boundaries

- Microservice internal URL (env MICROSERVICE_INTERNAL_URL) allows the app to call the microservice in-cluster
- Health endpoints: app/server/routes/health/live.get.ts and ready.get.ts are used for K8S probes and CI rollout verification
- Admin-only APIs under app/server/api/admin/* (guarded by requireAdmin.ts)

## Persistence

- MySQL 8 (docker-compose.yaml; .devcontainer/docker-compose.yml mirror) with utf8mb4
- Prisma migrations stored under app/prisma/migrations. Microservice keeps its own migrations under microservice/prisma/migrations (subset/simplified schema)
- Field encryption metadata comments live inline in schema.prisma (/// @encrypted etc.)

## Deployment

- Dockerfiles: app/Dockerfile, microservice/Dockerfile (multi-stage, PNPM, prisma generate during build)
- GitHub Actions: build images to gcr.io (Workload Identity federated auth), then apply .deploy/dineros.template.yaml via .github/actions/deploy-dineros-gke
- Staging CronJob for DB key rotation (runner-keyrotate image target) with RBAC manifests in .deploy/key-rotation-*.template.yaml
